author: Alex Frangos
title: Singapore Dollar Whipped by China Headwinds
text:
The world’s currencies are caught between the vise of the rising U.S. dollar and the turbulent Chinese yuan. Singapore’s dollar should be feeling the squeeze.
The Asian trading hub saw its dollar swoon last week when China let the yuan fall. It has since stabilized along with the yuan, but the condition of Singapore’s economy—and forces beyond its control—could mean more downward pressure on the horizon.
